    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, \"survive to feel it\"? i dont get that. if the art requires the absolute limit, then staying alive just feels like diluting the truth of the piece. isnt the most honest expression the moment when the artist and the art become indistinguishable, even if that moment is terminal? like, isnt there a certain purity in a tragedy that can never be undone or repeated?",
